The paper deals with the representation of planar graphs using rectilinear polygons, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of maximal planar graphs and Hamiltonian graphs suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.DS, cs.GT). The construction of area-universal rectangular layouts involves combinatorial optimization, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the use of numerical iteration and hill-climbing heuristics suggests a connection to computational optimization (cs.SI).
